classes.comment:
Class for custom beforeAll, beforeEach, afterEach and afterAll code.
beforeAll is automatically run during TestSuite.isStarted() function.
beforeEach is automatically run by core TestSuite assertions, but must be manually run in custom assertion tests.
afterEach is automatically run by core TestSuite assertions, but must be run manually in custom assertion tests.
afterAll is automatically run during TestSuite.delete() function, at the end of the scope for the TestSuite.

methods.label: afterAll
methods.comment: Code to run after all assertions have been completed.
methods.codesample:
Private a as Integer
Private b as Integer
 
Class IntegerIncrementBeforeAfter As AbstractCustomBeforeAfter
    
    Sub beforeAll()
        a = 0
        b = 0
    End Sub
    
    Sub beforeEach()
        a++
    End Sub
    
    Sub afterEach()
        b++
    End Sub
    
    Sub afterAll()
        Print |a is | & a & |, b is | & b
    End Sub
End Class

methods.label: runAfterEach
methods.comment: Tests whether a AbstractCustomBeforeAfter has been passed in and, if so, calls afterEach. Triggered from automatically all in-built assertions.
methods.codesample:
Dim globInt as Integer
Class IntegerIncrementer as AbstractCustomBeforeAfter
    Sub beforeEach()
        a = a + 1
    End Sub
    Sub afterEach()
        Print &quot;Finished test&quot;
    End Sub
End Class
Private Class CustomTester as AbstractCustomTester
    Function runTests as Boolean
        Dim incrementer as New IntegerIncrementer()
        Call Me.testSuite.addCustomBeforeAfter(incrementer)
        Call Me.testSuite.checkStarted()
       
       Call Me.testSuite.runBeforeEach()   &apos; Increments a global variable
       Call Me.testSuite.describe(&quot;Test global variable&quot;).assertEqualsInteger(1, globInt)
       Call Me.testSuite.runAfterEach()
    End Function
End Class
